commText: Warner and Mitchell Marsh are at the crease. Warner is on strike. Sam Curran will open the attack
Sam Curran to Warner, 1 run, angles in, Warner nudges the ball down on to the on-side for a single. The batter was falling over as the ball angled in

Sam Curran to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, poor delivery, on the pads, Mitchell Marsh gets behind the line of the delivery and clips it fine past short fine for a four. Delecatable from Mitchell Marsh to get off the mark

Sam Curran to Mitchell Marsh, FOUR, poor stuff from Sam Curran as he strays on to the pads of the batter. Mitchell Marsh gets inside the line of the delivery and clips it to the left of the short fine fielder this time. Sam Curran needs to alter his line a little
Sam Curran to Mitchell Marsh, no run, fuller length delivery, around 130 kph mark, Mitchell Marsh gets a stride out and punches the drive on the up. Rabada at mid-off dives to his right and stops it
Sam Curran to Mitchell Marsh, wide, slips one down leg. Wided. Poor delivery from Sam Curran and Mitchell Marsh didn't try anything fancy
Sam Curran to Mitchell Marsh, no run, gives the bowler the charge and drives on the up. That was delivered at 134.5 kph and ended up finding the man at cover
Sam Curran to Mitchell Marsh, no run, angles it across around 130 clicks, Mitchell Marsh gets back and across to stab it down into the deck
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Warner, no run, short, wide, Warner slaps the ball away and finds cover point. The room was there but Warner was a little circumspect
Arshdeep Singh to Warner, no run, gets the ball to angle in at the sticks at 130.6 clicks. Warner gets behind it and pats it down into the deck
Arshdeep Singh to Warner, SIX, short ball, Warner accepts it gleefully and slams it over deep square for a sixer. That was a poor ball and sat up for it to be slammed away. First sixer off the game
Arshdeep Singh to Warner, FOUR, gets the room outside off and slams it wide of the man at cover point. That was hit hard and into the gap. Warner gets his first four as well
Arshdeep Singh to Warner, no run, stabs a length delivery into the off-side
Arshdeep Singh to Warner, wide, too wide, Warner goes for a slash and misses. Has been wided
Arshdeep Singh to Warner, no run, goes for a booming drive and gets beaten. Lovely floaty length delivery at 130 kph and Warner looks to drive but gets beaten
Kagiso Rabada, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Rabada to Mitchell Marsh, wide, banged in short, well down leg, Mitchell Marsh lets it go and has been wided

Rabada to Mitchell Marsh, SIX, short ball, down on to the left shoulder, Mitchell Marsh gets hold of the delivery and slams the pull over deep backward square. Huge hit indeed. The Delhi openers are on a roll
Rabada to Mitchell Marsh, no run, gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it out into the off-side with soft hands

Rabada to Mitchell Marsh, leg byes, FOUR, leg byes or off the bat? Leg byes it is. Short once again. What's this fetish with the short ball? Looked to pull and missed it. The ball went off the side of ribs and into the fence. The keeper tried to fetch it back and gave it a valiant chase
Rabada to Mitchell Marsh, no run, looks to slap that through the off-side and bottom-ends the ball down into the off-side
Rabada to Mitchell Marsh, leg byes, 1 run, angled on to the pads, Mitchell Marsh misses the nudge. The ball falls off the pads into the on-side for a single
Rabada to Warner, no run, short ball, at 141.1 kph, Warner climbs up on to his toes and stabs it down into the off-side

Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell Marsh, SIX, the ball has gone on a long journey. Fuller ball at 129 kph and Mitchell Marsh thumps it over long-off. He had a astill head and Mitchell Marsh just went through with the shot
Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell Marsh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Mitchell Marsh, out Caught by Rahul Chahar!! Gone! Six and gone. Fuller ball, outside off, Mitchell Marsh goes for a boomin drive and slices it to find the man at cover point. Simple take for Chahar despite the fact it was travelling at a fast clip. First one down. Arshdeep Singh delivers the wicket for his team like he does so many times. Wasn't a great delivery but Mitchell Marsh failed to get enough elevation on it. He was looking good but has to go now. Warner was equally gutted at the other end. Mitchell Marsh c Rahul Chahar b Arshdeep Singh 20(12) [4s-2 6s-2]
Shai Hope, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh to Shai Hope, no run, fuller length delivery, Shai Hope drives on the up and finds the man at cover
Arshdeep Singh to Shai Hope, no run, goes round the wicket and bowls a slower one at 127 clicks. Shai Hope clips the ball down to mid-wicket as he picked up the slower delivery a little late
Arshdeep Singh to Shai Hope, no run, goes over the wicket and angles it away at 130 clicks. Shai Hope looks to tap it down but gets an inside edge on to the deck
Arshdeep Singh to Shai Hope, 1 run, slower delivery, outside off, Shai Hope stabs it down with soft hands and gets a single. He is off the mark
Rabada to Shai Hope, no run, steers a length delivery away, finds the man at short third
Rabada to Shai Hope, 1 run, short, wide, Shai Hope slashes it and gets away with it. Livingstone was after it and cuts it off at the deep point region. Only a single
Rabada to Warner, no run, uhhhhh! Inside edge. Warner wanted to across the line and gets an inside edge. The ball evaded the sticks
Rabada to Warner, FOUR, slower offie, angling away, Warner lets the hands to do the talking. Slaps it wide of the man at mid-off for a four

Rabada to Warner, SIX, wow! Warner plays an amzing shot. Walks across, sits down, gets hold of the length delivery and scoops it over short fine. Superb hit indeed. Superb innovation from the southpaw. Fifty up for the Delhi unit
Rabada to Warner, no run, gets the ball to angle away, Warner looks to dab it and misses. Was beaten on the inside edge
Harpreet Brar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Over Summary 1-5 Marsh starts with a couple of fours Warner too starts with boundaries Marsh pulls Rabada for a big six The dangerous Marsh falls to Arshdeep After 5 overs, DC are 51/1
Harpreet Brar to Shai Hope, no run, flatter one, angles it in, stabbed back to the bowler
Harpreet Brar to Shai Hope, no run, looks to back away and punch it as that was tossed up at 85.5 kph. The batter inside edges the ball down into the deck
Harpreet Brar to Shai Hope, 1 run, goes for a slog sweep, finds the man at deep mid on the bounce. That wasn't timed. Shai Hope not looking great out there
Harpreet Brar to Warner, no run, slightly shortish, outside off, stabbed down to the man at cover
Harpreet Brar to Warner, 1 run, dropped short, Warner goes back and slaps the pull down to long-on for a single

Harpreet Brar to Shai Hope, 1 run, excellent over from Harpreet Brar comes to an end. Was a tossed up delivery, Shai Hope drives it wide of the man at cover for a single. The powerplay is over. Time for some consolidation
Rahul Chahar, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, 1 run, drops it short, outside off, slashed down to deep cover for a single
Balls taken by David Warner to hit his first six \nIPL 2023: 247 balls (seven innings) \nIPL 2024: 4 balls
Rahul Chahar to Warner, 1 run, on the sticks, not much turn, tucked down to deep mid for a single
Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, 1 run, waits for the turn, slaps it down to deep cover for a single

Rahul Chahar to Warner, 1 run, good call from Hope to turn down the second. Was a flatter one, on the pads, Warner nudged it off the pads and called for two. The man at deep mid charged in and cut it off
Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, SIX, tossed up delivery, Shai Hope dances down the track and slaps it over long-on. Huge hit and Shai Hope has managed to get off to a decent start now

Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, FOUR, misfield by the man at point. Should have been a dot ball. Now it's a four. Was a short ball, Shai Hope slashed it down and the man at point let it through his legs. Poor work
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to Warner, FOUR, Harshal starts with a fuller ball, outside off, Warner gets the bat down after a forward press to slam the drive past cocer. The man at deep cover had no chance
Harshal Patel to Warner, no run, nails the yorker, was angled across, Warner jams the ball down into the off-side
Harshal Patel to Warner, no run, fuller length delivery, Warner drives the ball away to find the man at cover. The open stance from Warner has so far allowed him to open up the off-side a bit more
Harshal Patel to Warner, 1 run, shortish ball, outside off, slashed wide of cover for a single
Harshal Patel to Shai Hope, 1 run, nails the yorker, outside off, Shai Hope jams the ball out and the man at mid-off cuts it off. They get a single

Review taken. Seems to have come off gloves. UltraEdge taking some time to load. Happened yesterday as well. Was a shorter, slower ball and Warner couldn't control the pull. There is a clear spike. Warner has to go. The cameo ends.
Harshal Patel to Warner, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Warner, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Sharma and Harshal Patel were confident. Dhawan as well. Was a shorter and slower ball, the batter wanted to pull but was undone by the lack of pace and the hint of extra bounce. The edge was found and the keeper dived forward to take it. Warner was looking good but has to go now. Delhi would be disappointed. Both their openers looked but have had to go back. Warner c Jitesh Sharma b Harshal Patel 29(21) [4s-3 6s-2]
Rishabh Pant, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Harpreet Brar [1.0-0-3-0] is back into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Shai Hope, 1 run, drops it short, slashed down to deep cover for a single
Harpreet Brar to Pant, no run, drops it short, wide, outside off, Pant slashes the ball down and finds the man at point
Harpreet Brar to Pant, 1 run, plants his front foot forward and clips the ball down to deep mid for a single. Was a flatter one at the sticks
Harpreet Brar to Shai Hope, 1 run, was a flatter one, Shai Hope punches it wide of the man at cover. They settle for a single as Pant turned down the second
Harpreet Brar to Pant, 1 run, walks down the track and nudges it down to deep mid for a single
Harpreet Brar to Shai Hope, 1 run, flatter, quicker, Shai Hope pats it down to long-on for a single
Time for a time-out. DC will have to rework their plans a little. The wicket of Warner has pegged them back a little. But such an emotional moment for them. I0$
Rahul Chahar [1.0-0-14-0] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, no run, stabs the ball down to cover
Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, FOUR, tossed up delivery, Shai Hope sits down and slams the slog sweep to thread the ball into the gap. The men at deep square and deep mid were bisected with elan
Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, 1 run, mistimes the pull down to deep mid for a single
Rahul Chahar to Pant, no run, gets beaten in flight but the pads save him. That was a tossed up delivery, dipped on the batter and Pant missed the heave across the line. The pads came in handy
Rahul Chahar to Pant, 1 run, and brings out the reverse, finds the man at short third. Gets a single as Rabada was off-balanced
Rahul Chahar to Shai Hope, 1 run, goes back and nudges the ball down to deep long-on for a single
Kagiso Rabada [2.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Over summary 6-10 Brar bowls a tight last over of the powerplay Hope smashes Chahar for six and a four Harshal dismisses Warner in his first over After 10 overs DC are 86/2
Rabada to Shai Hope, 1 run, on a length and angling back into the right-hander, nudged down to long-on for a single
Rabada to Pant, 1 run, short of a good length and angling back into the left-hander - Pant is slightly cramped as he arched back on the cut, stabbed it square on the off-side for a single

Rabada to Shai Hope, SIX, hammered, Hope is on a roll after a slow start - back of a length and just outside off, he clears his front leg and then hoists it high and wide of long-on, sailed away into the stands
Rabada to Shai Hope, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rabada to Shai Hope, out Caught by Harpreet Brar!! Rabada has his man now - pitched up just outside off, Hope stayed leg-sided on the drive, doesn't get it off the middle of the bat and hence can't keep it down, was low and in front of cover - Brar dives forward, gets both hands and holds on. The Capitals lose a third well-set batter. Shai Hope c Harpreet Brar b Rabada 33(25) [4s-2 6s-2]
Ricky Bhui, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rabada to Bhui, no run, short of a good length and well wide of off, pushed off the back-foot to the off-side
Rabada to Bhui, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, steered backward of square on the off-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to Bhui, 1 run, a high full-toss from Chahar - Bhui comes down the pitch and swings it towards deep mid-wicket for a single

Rahul Chahar to Pant, FOUR, a chance and Harshal Patel didn't pick it, was a long hop and Bhui rocked back on the pull - hit it hard and to the left of the fielder - was Harshal looking into the sun? He definitely didn't see it coming and makes a half-hearted clasp, missing the ball by some distance
Rahul Chahar to Pant, 1 run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, whipped in front of square on the on-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to Bhui, no run, tossed up on off, defended solidly by Bhui
Rahul Chahar to Bhui, 1 run, slower and on off, eased down to long-off for a single
Rahul Chahar to Pant, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Pant gets down low and sweeps it past square leg for a single
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-6-1] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Pant, 2 runs, back of a length and on the hips, tucked behind square on the on-side and Pant is back for the second
Harshal Patel to Pant, FOUR, crisp, fuller length delivery outside off - a wide half-volley and Pant drills the drive through extra-cover, no one moved as the ball raced away
Harshal Patel to Pant, 2 runs, Harshal keeps it full and wide of off - Pant runs down the pitch and toe-ends the drive over cover, comes back for the second
Harshal, from round the wicket
Harshal Patel to Pant, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Pant, out Caught by Bairstow!! That's a soft soft dismissal - slower short ball angling into the left-hander, Pant arched back on the ramp past the keeper, but he has no pace to work with, ended up dabbing a dolly into the hands of Bairstow at backward point. As has been the case, the Capitals keep losing wickets just when their batter seemed well-set. Pant c Bairstow b Harshal Patel 18(13) [4s-2]
Tristan Stubbs, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Tristan Stubbs, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, punched straight to the fielder at mid-off
Harshal Patel to Tristan Stubbs, no run, slower short ball outside off - Stubbs was through with the shot early, the ball catches the toe-end and rolls thjrough to the keeper
Harpreet Brar [2.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Bhui, no run, tossed up on off, pushed back at the bowler
Harpreet Brar to Bhui, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harpreet Brar to Bhui, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Loud shout for caught behind, it's given as a wide, but Jitesh Sharma is confident and PBKS have reviewed. Flatter and down leg, Bhui was shaping for the paddle. Did he get an edge? Yes, there's a spike when the ball is next to the bat - clearly bat involved and the on-field call has been reversed. Bhui is OUT. A lucky wicket, but PBKS will not complain - was darted down leg and Bhui was looking to help it on its way with the fine paddle. Bhui c Jitesh Sharma b Harpreet Brar 3(7)
Axar Patel, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Harpreet Brar to Axar, FOUR, edged, but there's no slip and the ball runs away to the ropes - pushed through quicker and sliding with the angle, drew Axar into the push, he did look to open the face, but it was a genuine outside edge
Harpreet Brar to Axar, 1 run, dropped short and wide of off, cut away square on the off-side for a single
Harpreet Brar to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, Stubbs backs away and cuts it to deep cover for a single
Harpreet Brar to Axar, no run, appeal for LBW, but it has pitched well outside leg, Axar was shaping for the lap sweep and missed
Arshdeep, from round the wicket
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Tristan Stubbs, no run, on a good length and just outside off, defended back at the bowler
Arshdeep Singh to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, length ball angling into the right-hander, pushed in front of mid-on for a quick single
Arshdeep Singh to Axar, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven crisply and straight to the fielder at mid-off
Arshdeep Singh to Axar, 2 runs, back of a length and just outside off - Axar gets enough power on the cut to clear the leaping fielder at backward point, back for the second
Arshdeep Singh to Axar, FOUR, nicely played, short of a good length and well wide of off - Axar waits on it and then cuts it late, finds the gap square past point and beats the fielder in the deep
Arshdeep Singh to Axar, no run, tad fuller and just outside off, driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
Rahul Chahar [3.0-0-29-0] is back into the attack
Over summary 11-15 Rabada comes back and gets Hope Pant falls to Harshal trying to ramp Bhui is gone after a review After 15 overs DC are 124/5
Rahul Chahar to Tristan Stubbs, 1 run, tossed up on off, tucked behind square on the on-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to Axar, 1 run, tossed up on off, punched square on the off-side for a single
Rahul Chahar to Tristan Stubbs, 2 runs, Chahar tosses one just outside off - Stubbs backs away and then punches it in front of square on the off-side, comes back for the second
Rahul Chahar to Tristan Stubbs, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rahul Chahar to Tristan Stubbs, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! A gentle inside out chip, but Stubbs has played it a lot straighter and has holed out to long-on. Shahshank moves swiftly to his left, slides and completes a fine two-handed catch, the capitals continue to flounder. Stubbs was shaping to go inside out over cover, but Chahar cleverly held it back, forcing the right-hander to go a tad straighter. They've taken the strategic break at the fall of Stubbs. Tristan Stubbs c Shashank Singh b Rahul Chahar 5(8)
Sumit Kumar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rahul Chahar to Sumit Kumar, no run, pushed through by Chahar, punched back at the bowler

Rahul Chahar to Sumit Kumar, no run, Chahar tosses one just outside off, played with soft hands and to the left of cover - Sumit was a long way down the pitch looking for a run, but Axar ain't interested and sends him back
Kagiso Rabada [3.0-0-27-1] is back into the attack
Rabada to Axar, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, Axar plays close to his body and defends it to the off-side

Rabada to Axar, SIX, short, wide and just over Arshdeep for a maximum - width on offer and Axar threw his hands on the cut, gets a big edge and kept third man interested all along, only to go over his head and over the ropes
Rabada to Axar, 1 run, short and into the body, pulled down to long leg for a single
Rabada to Sumit Kumar, no run, back of a length and well wide of off, steered straight to the fielder at backward point
Rabada to Sumit Kumar, 1 run, slower short ball from Rabada, pulled past square leg for a single
Rabada to Axar, 1 run, short of a good length and angling back into the left-hander - Axar hops and drops it behind square on the off-side for a single
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-14-2] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Axar, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Harshal Patel to Axar, out Axar Run Out!! 1 run completed. An accurate throw at the keeper's end, the bails are broken and this could be close. Was Axar's call for the second and it's a bad call, he's short by a couple of yeards and DC have lost their 7th batter. Once again, a batter gets in and gets OUT for Delhi Capitals, Axar can't blame anyone for his dismissal though - short and into the body, he hopped across and tucked it past square leg, was always a risky second and Tanay's throw was right besides the stumps on the bounce. Jitesh Sharma breaks it and finds Axar well short. Axar run out (Thyagarajan/Jitesh Sharma) 21(13) [4s-2 6s-1]
Delhi Capitals have activated their impact substitute - Abishek Porel is the new man, he replaces Ricky Bhui
Abishek Porel, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, driven to the right of mid-off for a single
Harshal Patel to Sumit Kumar, leg byes, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, past Sumit Kumar's flick and rolls behind square on the on-side for a leg-bye
Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single
Harshal Patel to Sumit Kumar, 1 run, another slower short ball outside off - Sumit laps it through mid-wicket and wanted a second, sent back by his partner
Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, FOUR, nicely played, back of a length and well wide of off, pace on the ball and Porel slices the cut very fine, beating third man to his left
Arshdeep, from round the wicket
Arshdeep Singh [3.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Sumit Kumar, no run, slower short ball outside off - no pace to work with, Sumit throws his hands on the slap and is undone by the lack of pace, on the bounce to the keeper
Arshdeep Singh to Sumit Kumar, wide, the bouncer from Arshdeep, but it sails over Sumit's head and is called as a wide. PBKS though review and they've burnt one of them
Arshdeep Singh to Sumit Kumar, no run, short of a good length and just outside off - Sumit backs away on the slash and missed
Some disturbance behind the bowler and Sumit pulls out
Arshdeep Singh to Sumit Kumar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Sumit Kumar, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Edged and caught! The wickets keep tumbling for the Capitals - Arshdeep kept it full and just outside off, Sumit's feet went nowhere as he shaped for the big drive - lost his poise and the edge is gleefully accepted by Jitesh Sharma, who is having a good day behind the wicket. Sumit Kumar c Jitesh Sharma b Arshdeep Singh 2(9)
Kuldeep Yadav, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Arshdeep Singh to Kuldeep Yadav, 1 run, a direct hit at the bowler's end and Kuldeep had given up, set-off for a quick single after a dab to backward point, the ball bounced nicely into Bairstow's hands and he had a shy at the bowler's end
Arshdeep Singh to Abishek Porel, 1 run, slower short ball from Arshdeep, pulled down to long leg for a single
Arshdeep Singh to Kuldeep Yadav, no run, banged in short and at the stumps as Kuldeep backed away, he has a swish and missed
PBKS have brought their impact substitute - Prabhsimran Singh replaces Arshdeep Singh

Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, FOUR, nicely played, handy runs from DC's impact sub, banged in short and at the stumps - Porel swivels across and then pulls it over backward square leg for a boundary
Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, SIX, massive, slower ball on off - sits up and Porel prods forward, heaves it high and wide of mid-wicket - had a lot of height and plenty of distance as well
Harshal, from round the wicket
Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, FOUR, the boundaries keep coming - banged in short and down leg, Porel swivels across and then thumps the pull over backward square leg, bounced away to the ropes
Back to over the wicket

Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, FOUR, cheeky and four, a momentum changing over for DC - banged short and into the surface, Porel ride sthe bounce, opens the face of the bat and then runs it past third man, who was inside the ring

Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, SIX, smashed - Harshal is looking hapless now, slower ball at the stumps, but Porel has spotted it, swivels across and then bludgeons it over square leg for another maximum
Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Harshal Patel to Abishek Porel, out Kuldeep Yadav Run Out!! 1 run completed. A run-out to end the innings, but DC finish on 174 for 9 - fuller length delivery on off and was drilled down to long-on, never a second there, but they did chance the run, only to find Kuldeep Yadav well short when the stumps were broken. Still, 25 off the over and DC finish strongly. Kuldeep Yadav run out (Shashank Singh/Harshal Patel) 1(2)

17:16 Local Time, 11:46 GMT, 17:16 IST: That 25-run last over has helped Delhi Capitals finish on 174, a decent score on this surface, but PBKS will feel they've done well to restrict the Capitals to a low score. DC will look back at the scorecard and will think they'd too many batters who got a start and didn't convert it into a bigger score. Shai Hope was the top-scorer with 33, but it needed impact substitute Abishek Porel's last over onslaught to get them to a good total. PBKS were very disciplined with the ball and were backed well in the field - Two wickets each for Arshdeep and Harshal, though the latter's last over became the difference between chasing 155 and chasing 175 now. Can DC take the momentum into their bowling? They've used up their impact substitution and might be a bowler short. Back for the chase shortly..

Abishek Porel (translated from Hindi): I knew I was going in before 3 overs. And the support staff told me be ready as you are one of the impact players. I translated on the field today what I practiced before. My plan was to hit the ball where it came from. 174 is a good score and our bowling unit is good, so let's see.
Welcome back. DC players in high spirits with Warner doing a jig. Pant and Ishant joking around. Dhawan and Bairstow the openers. Khaleel to start off. A wide slip in.
